comment: This really heartbreaking. I've only met a narcissist once. The term was only new at that time and It was only because of a friend that I knew the term existed, but I didn't  know what it really meant. I suppose you can't until you experience it yourself. I met this woman who was a church lady who portrayed herself as this mothering mentor. The first time i met I didn't like her, but I thought I should give her a chance. She was intelligent and to begin with she was very kind. She saw what ever vulnerability was there and used it for her own agenda. They do this love bombing shit and I feel so stupid that I wasnt thinking more critically of the situation. There were so many times that I just sat there like WTF is going on but It took her threatening my son (who has been chronically unwell) for me to get to the point that I had enough. I feel so so stupid that it took that, I should have walked away the first time things seem really off. They know how to mind fuck and break you. The deeper you‚Äôre in the longer it takes to come back from that, and you will not come out the same person. For a long time I lost trust in myself. I never want to go through that again. but I'm glad I did, because it made me realise I need to change the way I portray myself. I needed to make sure I don't portray myself as a someone who is easily victimised, which isn't easy for someone who is shy. It made me mentally stronger. No matter who this behaviour is directed at, male or female, it's still abuse and never ever ok. It's never ok to manipulate, hurt (mentally or a physically), threaten, isolate, steal, and break people. Your victims deserved better, and you should be ashamed of yourself.

comment:
I hope he finds peace. I see a lot of myself in Johnny. I too was in an abusive relationship and eventually when she cheated I found the will to kick her to the kerb. We have two children together and now finally after 18 months of court I have majority custody of them. 

My ex still plays the victim even though she didn't work and I paid for everything. She says I hit her, financially abused her, sexually abused her - yet all the evidence I gave proved it to be false and she retracted these statements - amazing how she had no recourse for saying such horrendous things to me after being together for 9 years. She genuinely believes she is the victim even though she has caused all this pain on our daughters and me.

Sorry for oversharing, I just want people to know that this is quite a common situation and it is very hard for an empathetic man like me and Johnny to come to terms with abuse like this as we would never do it so we can't understand it.

comment:
I don't know why she's trying to ruin this man, she's probably done it to multiple other rich men, she already had millions and she's going to do it to the next guy she gets with, so in a very Italian-like voice, "take-it EC will ya?" Women can be so spiteful/merciless when they don't get what they want. It's scary. Hormones are a hellava drug. Not saying men can't be too, but women so it in such a way where they enjoy it essentially watching the other person die a slow, painful, proverbial death.

I'm not saying I believe either one of them more or less than the other, but either way, it's both of their faults that they allowed it to go on for so long. Then again, love makes you do crazy things. I just hate that one person in a relationship always loves the other person more than the other is almost always the case, whether it's a tiny amount or big, it's still there. He's lucky he didn't have kids with her or that $100 million would have been more like $500 million. I wonder how much money her ex made compared to Depp. You know where I'm going with this. What chick wouldn't want to get with a movie star for the money? $20 million is just not enough for some people, so I'm going to get with Johnny Depp and then divorce him and make $100 million.

I hate to be the one to judge because for one, I'm for sure not perfect and also, who am I to judge someone else, especially when I don't even know them? That being said, they both should've known eachother were poison to begin with if they both were so willing to leave their "significant other" for someone they just met. comment:
As soon as I saw Amber's clip in the court I was 100% sure that she was at fault. She was *eating,* talking about her "abuse" without getting tense and looking any different than unbothered. All of us that that had to go through domestic abuse understand the feeling of a dam breaking as soon as you uncover your experience. We try to force those memories away and tell ourselves that it's fine but as soon as somebody asks without brushing the topic off it's over.
People might react different but there's no way you'd neither cry, shiver, be tense, lose your voice or avoid eye contact. And there's no way you'd be able to eat *anything.*
Besides that she always ate when a difficult question was coming up so she could think some more but when there was a save question she'd just speak with her mouth full.

comment:
This all seems like scape goating. Why must one person be to blame? That's not how most toxic relationships work. That's not how any relationship works. Some people bring out the best and worst from us. The only difference is since they are celebrities, everything is magnified by like 1000x. Everything is in extremes once you pass a certain threshold of fame (or so it seems). No one is afforded a normal emotion or experience.
Back to Depp & Heard; the only thing I see are two people who are extremely toxic, for whatever reason, and acting accordingly. 
He is clearly struggling from substance issues & she has her issues...otherwise, why get with someone who is so excessive? When a person is destructive and toxic, they attract others who are just as destructive and toxic.
My hope for BOTH are that they get help! Real and serious help...if they can get it being the status they are. I hope Depp gets clean and stays sober. Not because he's an artist and I want to continue seeing his craft, but because he's a human being, he's a real person, and a father. Every person deserves to be their best self. Even if they've committed the mortal sin of FAME.
I don't know anything about her, maybe she's a good person, maybe not. But she was good enough for Depp to love at one point. So, I hope she gets herself together too.

comment:
I understand the allure that movie stars and celebrities have on regular people who live normal lives and work everyday etc and Johnny Depp is about as big as they come. But damn it if it‚Äôs not a crying shame that things like this can‚Äôt remain something of a private nature. When he puts himself in movies and other things it doesn‚Äôt mean he and others in the public eye are not entitled to a few areas of life that remain private. For those who salivate over the gossip of others I say to all of you , get a fucking life. 
That being said , to endure something like this isn‚Äôt so much an event but rather it‚Äôs a process. One which results in a broken heart that‚Äôs shattered in a way unlike broken hearts from losing a girlfriend etc and the healing of such is also not an event , again it‚Äôs a process. No doubt those shattered hearts can be mended , perhaps left to be somewhat calloused forever more thereafter. But the reward upon achieving this realization that puts the pieces back together is the deepest sense of peace one can achieve in this life short of being embraced by the Almighty himself. Not that it would ever be known or matter much but if I could wish one thing for this man it would be exactly that , PEACE ! Rest easy Johnny ! You‚Äôll be drowning in serenity as soon as you realize what is truly important in this life and celebrity status isn‚Äôt it.

comment:
The first time I seen A H in a movie callled, The Stepfather, I didn't like her. I thought she was a self centered terrible actress! I'm a pretty good character judge and not even half way through the movie, had to read the back of the DVD case to find out who she was. Prior to that movie, I'd never heard of her at all.  There was something about A H that just didn't sit right with me and after verbally speaking on her terrible acting in the movie and finding out her real name I had spoke on it to my other family members who were watching the movie also. 
The next time I remember hearing her name was in the trailer of Rum Diary. Now, I'm a very huge fan of Johnny Depp. I have seen all of his movies and read a lot about him and how his childhood was. I loved listening to his band's music. I loved watching all of his movies. So naturally when I heard of The Rum diary I was eager to watch it. When I was in the movie theater I had mentioned again to the person I was sitting with that, "She's a horrible actress. I don't like her at all" referring to A H when she came on the screen. After Rum Diary was over I almost felt sick to my stomach. I knew Johnny was in trouble. I could tell even in her so-called acting she was trying to seduce him and it was more than obvious she did not have good intentions. My opinion and character judging was totally on point. She was completely out to ruin Johnny! I was physically sick for almost a week after watching the movie Rum Diary. This actress who looked beautiful on the outside was a very horrible, angry, wicked, hateful, spiteful, evil, twisted, lost soul on the inside. She was digging into Johnny Depp's whole existence with everything inside of her. Like a serpent she was ready to devour him and I felt complete heartache for Johnny. He was consumed by her from the beginning and I seen it all. That is why I was so physically sick after leaving the theater. 
It wasn't long after that when I read about Johnny leaving Vanessa for 
A H that I realized my instincts, and opinions on this beautiful demon were completely on point! 
My thoughts and prayers are with Johnny now more than ever. He is a good man with a good heart. He did not see any of this coming at the beginning yet, I did. I'm so sorry Johnny that you were so misled by such evilness. I can't even imagine the helplessness you felt when you finally realized who A H really was and what she was about. If you ever read this Mr Johnny Depp, please no that I stand with you on your fight for justice. 
There is a war between Good and evil that has been going on a while.
But in the end, good will win!!
And evil will go out of style.
Hang in there. 
May God's Blessings always be upon you.
#justiceforjohnny
DeeDee~

comment:
As a survivor of Domestic Violence, with mended broken bones, bruises that no one ever saw-but a close few-verbal & physical abuse to the point I lost a 23 week baby. I can say with absolute certainty that an abuser shows their colors not only at home but in their work life also. They lay all the blame for their actions on the victim. They file court documents claiming the other person is violent, they bully anyone around them. They use your own insecurities against you. While you are scared they are powerful and they don‚Äôt stop trying to ruin you until you are beaten down on the verge of not standing up. The only way to rid yourself of them unfortunately is to stand up even when your knees buckle.

My point, Amber Herd as you can see by the interviews is a power and controlling, demanding person , who plays the victim without merit. Half of Hollywood is standing up for JD because they have worked with him. That actually means everything. 

When I stood in court against my ex my legs shook, my voice broke, i had tears in my eyes and was throwing up before being called up. I was scared beyond reason. I don‚Äôt know JD personally but I back him without question because he does not present the traits I know so well. I am ashamed that a man feels embarrassed when it comes to being abused. I am ashamed AH is getting away with trying to ruin his reputation. I am ashamed that Disney released him on one woman‚Äôs word. I‚Äôve watched him grow as an actor and I know abusive personalities to well unfortunately. As a survivor I back him 100%.

comment:
I am very glad this did not result in the tragedy that might have come of it.  It's never clear when you begin and sustain a toxic relationship that it's toxic, nor that you could meet the end of your life simply by loving someone who does not know what love looks like or how to live it.  He might have died. He's not necessarily safe now, nor will he be from now forward.  He's on her radar now & she's not a rational person. 
The only positive that can be found in their story is the real-time lived example of how domestic violence can happen in ANYONE'S life, most often the survivors of it feel more shame and responsibility for it than their abusers do and the trend is on the rise.  Teach our children what love looks like.  If you are not demonstrating that to them daily, if your friendships and partnerships show a tableau of what love is not; end the production, let that stage go dark.  Our babies deserve better than to be risked to re-living out a nightmare they never should have seen: in their own kitchens, in the house down the street, on television, in the diner after church on Sunday morning and in the aisles at Walmart, Target or Trader Joe's, there are examples of abuse everywhere and we all should know better by now.

The problem is, that when you happen to be on the outside, you tend to take her side because she is charismatic, yet the people who've known Johnny Depp for decades, *know* he's not the person she has made him out to be. The *sad* thing is, no one in her inner circle is stepping up to defend Johnny, because they are afraid she will attack them too. They know how ruthless she can be. This is the vicious cycle of Covert Narcissists. They honestly believe they are the victims, when in fact, the victim they see is not themselves... The victim is *actually* the person standing opposite them (hence the term "mirroring"). They pretend what their abused partner is experiencing is their own experience. I'm willing to bet that everything she has said he's done, *she* is the one who has done it to him. I hope he speaks out and I hope he is vindicated in court and in his personal and professional life. Just because she's a woman doesn't make her always right, even -- and maybe even *especially* -- in this Me Too age. *All* abuse victims should be able to speak out against their abusers. Men included.

comment:
A good friend of mine is a cousin of Depp's; Friend is one of a small handful of Depp's extended family with whom Depp is still on casual speaking terms (cos Friend doesn't constantly beg for money). 

Heard isn't his first abusive partner, she's just his most famous one. Like you said, he takes out his insecurities on himself, in the form of self-destructive behaviours. He's kind of always done this, and has poked fun at it, as a bit of a coping mechanism: see his old tattoo, which initially read "Winona Forever," but after he and Winona Ryder abruptly ended their engagement, he had the tatt altered to say "Wino Forever." Winona even has been amongst those who've defended Depp; their relationship was tumultuous and volatile, but they were also fairly young, neither in the greatest mental health state, and while they may have been unintentionally emotionally manipulative towards each-other, that's the thing, Depp & Ryder both recognised their relationship as _mutually toxic,_ and most importantly to Heard's perjury, neither Depp nor Ryder ever physically harmed the other. They're one of those pairs work well as friends (I believe he and Ryder did rekindle a friendship, when he was married to Vanessa), but as the kind of romantically devoted couple they were, almost thirty years ago, it was just too volatile.

I brought up so much of his relationship with Ryder, because it shows that when he's emotionally hurting, he turns his negative behaviour onto himself, rather than onto others. He's not the "abusive alcoholic," but the _abused alcoholic!_

comment: I fell in love with Johnny Depp as a child, when I secretly watched movies like "The Man Who Cried" and "Chocolat" on tv. While I - of course - don't have an inkling of what he is like in person, I can only guess by the way he treated the Taraf de Ha√Ødouks, Roma musicians whom he loves and respects. It takes a good man to treat a Rom like a human being, let alone a friend (I am from a nomadic group myself and have experienced first-hand how prejudiced and xenophobic people can be). The character of a man can be seen in how they treat marginalized groups. It breaks my heart to know that this woman treated him this way - no-one deserves domestic violence and abuse. I hope he heals, and will be able to open his heart to love again.

comment: Women can be sociopaths too! And with that said just as men, they can also be people with serious personality disorders, mood disorders, or a multitude of other mental health situations that have never been diagnosed or resolved. Everyone needs to remember we are all imperfect human beings. And we should all put our opinions aside and let those who actually KNOW the situation make the best decisions possible. I hope Depp is the lovely eccentric, talented man we‚Äôve all believed him to be. I hope AH isn‚Äôt being ignored! If a woman says she‚Äôs been mistreated, that should most definitely be taken Seriously and the perpetrator be held accountable. Or if she‚Äôs the abuser, than she should be punished and held at the same accountability as any abuser would. But y‚Äôall we do not know these people! They are entitled to go through this awful experience without everyone chiming in with opinions they know nothing about. Let‚Äôs be hopeful the truth comes to light just simply because fairness is important and good people deserve to be treated as so. Everyone has struggles. These are theirs. Let‚Äôs just hope that the right side is surrounded by love, protection, empathy and lots of smart people. And that the outcome will be eventually healthy and happy and peaceful for the ones hurt in this situation. These people are more than the movies they make for us. They deserve dignity of peace and privacy too. No matter their career. Peace and love to anyone who needs it. I mean that . Let‚Äôs try to encourage with love and less judgement.

comment:
The truth is still the truth... in that crazy boy toys, do in fact actually drive their significant others coocoo. At some point, a female clues into her reality of infidelity; lies; and narcissism. These are very real truths about being a male whom, does not or cannot settle in or commit to one attentive relationship.
In fact, the heart throb is someone many ppl envy.  But the outcomes of continually being groomed in this manner from a young age. These are the risks to in turn pursue women of the same backgrounds.
Women whom are emotionally charged without moral directive as a youth, easily misinterpret their own beliefs and personal experiences.  The hope in these situations, is that only life in maturity can teach the more average individual. Where men, whom can and do have any women they want.  Can of sorts, 'wake up', and thus appreciate a more stable lifestyle. It is tragic, that women tend to be at higher risk, to re-establish stability. Even than, the actual re-establishinv of psychological restructuring.  Is very intense and thoroughly guaranteed.
Therefore, if any child cannot or does not have proper parenting in place before hand, the cycles of inaccuracy are often much too overwhelming,  to overcome. So, whatever tragedies there are in inheritance, in even generations beforehand. The capacity to changes these or recognize them are very minimal.
As a First Nation Canadian mother, I myself stay hopeful... I advocate from a family level. And I under took the psychological changes that I needed, in order to thrive. I see the adversity firsthand against my children. And my reasoning for not conforming to unhealthy people, is commonly despised. Thankfully, for myself, I grew up with a sense of reasoning compassion and wisdom for right and wrong. Where, I have been able to seemingly avoid direct dysfunctions and keep a clear perspective about truth.
In contrast to this however, I do in fact suffer immensely with isolation effects. I dont have very severe symptoms of doubt. But now that I have matured, I do question my motives of vanity in opposition to family violence. So technically, I have similar struggles to which I do in fact identify.  Where vanity as an onset, does play a role in my capacity to cope. Which, in contrast, my own reasoning for companionship is from the second nature of my family life struggles.
I, commit very devotingly to a healthy and safe home, for my children. Where the only true saving grace, that I can believe in, is in fact the truth.  When people are abusive, and tend to blame and lie, rather than interpretion themselves in the situation.  It just seems more protective and humane, to speak about problems from beginning to end, with healthy outcomes as the benefactor. I feel like, if my children learnwhy it is important to choose the right. Than the possibilities of firgiveness and in meeting good people in the world. Is their best allie. I dont know what the mental health risks are for, the very real levels of disruption that I have been living with, along side unwell family members. 
It actually seems horrifying. And I think this is another area where, even my children knowing the reality of human life at home, in the family. Are better than living at risk. Thinking that ppl and life situations are normal, when they are not.
As our own family unit. We stay hopeful through volunteering and donating food to the essential workers, whom spend a lot of time away from their own homes and families.
We have a little area of loving appreciation from the faces in the community we often see.and its so nice to bting that light in their smiles, when they see us! I am never short of conversations to revelate my belonging.
Perhaps one day, I can at least forgive the anger and unwellness in my own upbringing, that I am unable to allow in my own life.
My parents have been separated since I was 3, I am the product of the end of their first marriages and former families. My father continued on with addictional relationships and children. Where his life long struggle with depression and racism, ended within the dis-unity of his own home, where his health complications were far beyond manageable.
I have always been deeply in love with my dad, and my siblings, to which I find the truth much more soothing to know the reality of the problematic circumstances by which I struggle with. I know God is real, and I do not blame the Father son and the Holy Spirit üíú Thank you.

comment: I've been a fan of Johnny Depp since Jump Street.  I've heard of him spontaneously showing up at hospitals as Capt. Jack, tipping thousands to waiters and waitresses who took care of him and the film crew, kind to his fans.  I don't know the man personally but everything AH has said doesn't fit how Johnny Depp comes across.  He's real and transparent, as in this is my life, i don't need your say so kind of transparent and he doesn't seem to be one of those stars that changes when a camera goes on.  There are a few things a woman can say concerning men that are straight up jaw dropping, stop you in your tracks, accusatory type stuff, that are default believed; damn near regardless of truth.   I wasn't there, I don't know what really happened, but people that have known JD for decades flat said it's not him and completely out of his character.  People who don't necessarily like the man defended him.  That says something.  Having said that AH was obviously wounded, hurt, and maybe she wanted to do the 'hurt you back and make you feel like i felt' thing....i don't know.  But as a fan it doesn't seem like a complete story of the accusations that she's making from her side is forthcoming....it's like a criminal in the interrogation room or on the stand in court.  That criminal may have had a gun in his or her hand, so to speak, but they're going to downplay their role and point the finger elsewhere.  I have a feeling that's what's going on here.  Just my opinion

comment:
Lord, what a saint Depp is if you listen to this. 

Couldn‚Äôt be that his infamous huge alcohol and drug abuse problems might have caused him to say and do regrettable violent things that pushed her buttons and drove her to slap/hit him in retaliation? 

Man, it takes two to tango in a good and in a bad marriage. It‚Äôs rarely and maybe never, 100% one person‚Äôs fault. In my line of work I‚Äôve seen many a marriage crumble and if you want the truth, it‚Äôs usually somewhere in the middle, with both parties accusing the other and doing their best to make themselves look better. 

They made the decision to try their cases in public in the English court, which requires celebrity rags prove things like, ‚Äúwife beater‚Äù accusations. In America, the accused has to prove their innocence - a much tougher row to hoe. 

In the end, after all the testimonies and evidence was presented at trial, the court ruled: Yes indeed - Depp is a wife beater and yes, indeed Heard responded in kind. 

It‚Äôs pretty obvious now that both contributed to a very unstable and violent marriage. 

And why is it, that even women in the Me Too movement, blame Heard for ‚Äúbreaking up a good marriage,‚Äù when she and Depp had an affair? 

Why wasn‚Äôt Depp demonized for destroying his own long term relationships with 6 different partners, the latest being his faithful wife, Venessa Paradis. 

But it‚Äôs still always the conniving woman who gets the blame as if men just can‚Äôt help themselves when tempted. 

In a hilarious and over-the-top case of hypocrisy, I read where he accused Heard of sleeping with all her costars after him and he just didn‚Äôt trust her. No duh, Sherlock. 

Just say ‚ÄúNo!‚Äù Johnny! Just say no. 

You are another casualty of the Me Too spotlight and there are not enough lawyers or piles of cocaine or bottles of alcohol to make your ‚Äúwife beater‚Äù label go away and if the rehab doesn‚Äôt work, you‚Äôll sadly be your drunken swashbuckling alter ego for real - minus all the cool adventures. The wacky compass is in your hands.

comment:
Here's a good life tip... if you're in a relationship with someone and you've got kids, as well as the relationship has lasted for many years... don't go hooking up with someone else, because you will inevitably ruin your already good thing. This is for men and women. Nobody respects the sanctity of marriage anymore and things happen. The facts are that when you walk away from someone, which whom its already been going so well with, you never know what you're going to end up with. There's no crystal ball to see the hell you're possibly walking into. 

With that being said... I wish the best for Johnny, because I've always been a fan. Until all this mess began with her, I never even knew who she was. I've been in a few messed up relationships myself, and I can definitely say that... I stand with Johnny. 

I do not condone a man hitting a woman, unless it really comes down to self defense. A man has absolutely got to have no choice, because he's backed into a corner,  there's a weapon involved, and the woman needs to be actively trying to injure or kill the man. If the man can walk out of the house and get somewhere, then he is still in control. So if he did hurt her in any way, and it was in absolute self defense, then fine. If he hurt her and had a way to leave before it got that far, I can't just say he gets a free not in trouble card, but I understand that if someone is pushing all your buttons and being ruthless, that eventually something is bound to happen. I'm not 100% about all the details from start to finish, but based on what I feel I understand is that she is narcissistic and overall being with her had changed him in a negative way. Anyone who really knew him seemed to notice that he wasn't the same. It was an unfortunate way to find out the grass wasn't greener on the other side, but I'm glad he made it out. 

We need to water our own grass. When we're too busy watering our own lawn, we don't care about what's going on in someone else's yard.

comment:
Hell.... I even fell in love with Amber when I saw her in Drive Angry and her performance as Mera in Aquaman solidified that... but NOW, those movies (which I ADORE because of their coolness and stories) become harder to watch, because of what a horrible person and role model this monster of a woman has become. I believed Johnny from the start, not because he is a "man", but because I actively watched his career and life for over 20 years now and all I've seen is a humble, generous and talented actor, who has his rockstar phases with a drink to many and some drugs (like what, 50% of Hollywood?), but never have I heard serious accusations against him. The "me too" movement has done some good, no doubt, but this is a case where it is contorted beyond what it stands for and makes something terrible out of it, by using it to actively hurt and destroy people! 

I still sincerely hope that Johnny gets back on his feet, and can gets the respect he deserves (and not being let down by Disney and Warner Brothers who made BILLIONS from him and sided with Amber, just because she is a "woman"). Amber NEEDS TO BE PUNISHED as an example, that the movement is NOT to be used to hurt men, but to find real justice, based on proof and facts, which is the basis for THE LAW! Look at Harvey Weinstein... those are the real monsters among men!

Hang in there Johnny. You have millions of fans who believe in you and wish you the best!

comment: I find that his relationship with his mother is the key and the answer to this whole ordeal, and very revealing of his true character. Men are often teased by other men and women for being a "mama's boy", but these are the same types of men that many little girls dream about marrying when they are little, and they also make the best buddies (friends) for other men, because of the "feminine" qualities they pick up and learn from their mothers. This is something to think about the next time someone hears the phrase "mama's boy", and it is also found on the other side of the spectrum in the phrase "daddy's girl", but they both breed very different types of people that is exposed in their very definitions. I am always trying to discover an actors true character revealed in acting roles, it is a sort of hobby, and many times this is also their breakout roles, and often seen as and said by critics to be an Oscar worthy or award nominated and winning performance. I believe they stand out in these roles because it isn't really acting for them and they are largely themselves in these roles. For Johnny I think "Edward Scissorhands" is the closest to Johnny that a person can get, and I can't imagine "Eddy" doing any of this he is accused of. Do I think he is a perfect angel, certainly not, but I don't think he is a "Mort Rainey" either. I really hope he ends up "Finding Neverland".

comment:
As a victim of abuse by my ex girlfriend. It just sucks honestly. 
I wasn't afraid to speak up because I was afraid.
I was afraid to because I was embarrassed and did not want to face the humiliation of admitting that I was allowing a girl to treat me that way.
The reality is I never should have looked at it in that way. Physical and mental abuse grinds you down and makes it even harder to break away the longer you wait to speak up. Don't be afraid, the consequences of not doing so are worse than trying to convince yourself what you put yourself through is okay. 
You're not alone, I've been there and almost payed for it; the resulting depression during and even after almost made me take my life and I am still here.
Things will get better.

comment:
Shits hard to deal with,  my ex only hit me a couple times,  nothing serious,  and during the relationship I always just chalked it up to an emotional explosion.  It wasn't until a year of being single that I began to recognize the emotional abuse, I endured after having a girl I was dating having enough of my mannerisms and finally asked "why do you always apologize, you didn't do anything wrong,  I'm not even upset with you"  I'm facing divorce,  she wants the kids and child support when I have been raising them on my own for the entire year.   It wasn't until last month that she started to actually take the kids every other weekend. 

I'm scared because,  I know if I were a woman,  this would be an open and shut case,  I'd have whatever custody I desire and the ability to claim child support etc.  All I want is what's best for my kids which is at most joint custody, but as a man,  I know I am facing a gauntlet and it sucks.    

Sorry for my rant,  but I bottle this stuff up too much and Johnny's story is relatable

comment:
His nature is that of an abuse victim, not wanting to persevere through the relationship. In relationships, the abuser will often manipulate and gaslight the victim into believing they are at fault, cutting them off from friends and fam, and love bombing periodically to ensure the victim believes the relationship can be salvaged. I believe that saying Johnny Depp only stayed because he‚Äôs a good man has some validity, but it also trivializes his trauma he experienced from Amber. 

I worked at a crisis shelter for battered women, and in training, we were taught how to recognize signs of spousal abuse. As we were only by phone, and another part of the group dealt with the women in person, we were taught how to recognize signs through just their words through a phone call. In my opinion, the recording of Amber telling Johnny she ‚Äújust hit him‚Äù is both gaslighting (trying to convince him he‚Äôs not hurt because it ‚Äúwasn‚Äôt a punch,‚Äù trying to downplay her own actions by saying she only ‚Äúhit‚Äù him, trying to convince him it‚Äôs HIS fault because she just ‚Äúgets so mad,‚Äù and blaming her actions on something else) and obvious proof that she is the abuser in the relationship. 

The actual audio is much more telling as to revealing her tone and Johnny‚Äôs: she is annoyed/angry and he is placating/calm. He‚Äôs trying to de-escalate her anger to avoid harm. As for his plea for help in 2016, that‚Äôs literally a cry for help. He used a MILLION buzz words signaling he needs help without directly saying it. (Not directly stating help is needed is actually common as victims struggle to even admit there‚Äôs a problem. Once they do, they hope that the problem with resolve itself, when in the meantime, they lose potential friends/family that could help them from the situation as well as begin to feel trapped.) 

Something that seems so easy like ‚ÄúWell just leave!‚Äù Is much more complicated than it seems. There‚Äôs the issue of having children together, shared finances, fear of societal isolation, etc. For Johnny, it could be the fear of this exact scenario happening as it did. He feared people not believing him and losing his career over it. 

TL;DR ‚Äî‚Äî Justice for Johnny Depp. Poor man deserves help ‚ù§Ô∏è

(Also, I am NOT a professional psychologist/psychiatrist/therapist/anything else, so if I‚Äôm wrong, feel free to add! I only have training through the organization that I worked for!)

comment:
So here we go.

I never wanted kids, a women messaged me on Facebook whom I knew of. We agreed to be friends with benefits. She asked and I vividly remember her saying to me ‚Äúso you never want kids?‚Äù.

I said no.

She was on the pill, then she told me ‚ÄúI‚Äôm not trapping you, but I forgot to take the pill‚Äù. I bit the bullet then went along with it, I was suggesting all these options and she kept saying no to them all. 

(I should say that at some point previous weeks prior that she would even go to a sperm bank).

She was close to 30 and she said she was getting to age where it‚Äôs too old to have kids, so she says she‚Äôs pregnant and saying no to all of my suggestions on how to juggle parenting. She said ‚Äúno‚Äù.

She wanted to have the baby on her side of the West Country, the day before the due date I suggested to stay with her as it could happen at any time. She said....‚Äùno‚Äù I got no signs yet.

Next day? You can‚Äôt even write this, the baby was born. Two people was around her, her mum and auntie. Not one point did they think to message me, call me.

I miss the birth.

I wasn‚Äôt allowed to stay on the ward cause men are not allowed too. I had no money to stay anywhere, her mum left the hospital and I had to basically beg the ward to stay inside because it was late and I had no where to go?!

They let me stay thank fuck. 

Then next day I had to leave to go home and regroup and get changed.

I call the mother and ask to see my daughter, she said ‚Äúno‚Äù and ‚ÄúI‚Äôm busy that day‚Äù and ‚ÄúI‚Äôll let you know‚Äù. 

She finally agrees to a day so I did, I offer to change the nappy and she said ‚Äúno I‚Äôll do it‚Äù her mother smiled with a smerk and they both took her in the kitchen and I was just left in the front room alone.

That day I just thought ‚Äúwhat the fuck am I even doing here?‚Äù.

So I just left them to it.......no I‚Äôm not on the birth certificate. Of course I‚Äôm not lol 

Oh......did I mention she‚Äôs now a lesbian?

Please, comments and replies to this and let me know your thoughts.

comment:
I obviously don't know what happened, and idolisation of celebrities can be misdirecting, but I have to say that I'm touched and hopeful because so many women in this comment section are siding with Depp.
I've met a lot of girls and women who were abusive, mentally and physically, two of them tried to blackmail their exes, two of them stalked their exes (to the extend of calling his boss to smear him) and two of them accused their boyfriend/husband of domestic violence, rape and molesting children.
It has been hellish for women for a long, long time to get protection and justice, but in modern times it became very easy for women to smear or even try to wreck the lives of men by making false accusations.

So to most of the women in this comment section: be careful of who you support, but thank you for showing you are on the side of the apparent victim, regardless of sex.
Luckily I'm no victim myself but I know what a broken and discredited man looks like.
Accused of the most unimaginably horrible things, scarred for life, robbed of their children and financially sucked dry.
Again, thank you.

comment:
Being a victim of domestic violence as a child and in both of my marriages (1st husband put me in a coma while trying to kill me kicking me repeatedly on the right side temple wearing steel toe boots. 2nd husband was mentally, verbally and emotionally abusive.), my heart cries for Johnny Depp everytime I hear about this. I grew up watching Johnny on tv. I first watched him on 21 Jump Street and Nightmare On Elm street then Edward Scissor hands. I've never missed one of his roles. 
Johnny Depp truly is one of the most respectful, loving, generous, caring & big hearted humans I've ever met. I remember seeing that interview for Alice & I remember feeling like something was not right with his answer. When he jokes or answers poetically, he smiles or smirks. When he sd what he did, you can literally see sadness & even a broken down man, in his eyes. 
Things like that should remind people that celebrities are people too & go through the same situations we do. 
I know that feeling of "wanting to go home" to well. "Home" is that one place where you feel safe, loved & of worth. Home is not the place where you live, it is the place where you feel whole & happy. 
I hope Johnny can one day find the peace & happiness he so much deserves.

comment: Abuse is abuse; women can be just as abusive as men. Demon possession is real. Leslie Vernick wrote a powerful book explaining the difference between a difficult marriage and a destructive marriage. In a difficult marriage, one or both parties may experience disappointment, but in a destructive marriage one person's personhood is being destroyed. It's not two sheep that are involved but rather a wolf and a sheep and wolves eat sheep. So sheep beware, get out, stay out. Be wary of crocodile tears and shows of remorse; it may just be a slaver trying to entice a runaway slave back. Forgiveness is a must, but it does not mean reconciliation, unless genuine change is evident.

comment: As a DV survivor one of the things even I was unaware of is how common DV is committed against Men. Sadly, just as frequently, it is actually the female who is the aggressor. Mr. Depp is an amazing actor. And he is a genuinely good and kind man in my opinion, which is based on interviews Ive seen and comments by those who know him, ever since AH began slinging her brand of false psychotic allegations. Hes been severely abused. I wish him all the best in his journey forward from all of this, and am glad he has lots of love and a solid support system surrounding him. God bless him, his family, and especially his ex wife for speaking up, telling the truth, and for supporting him during this. comment:
I believe they both sabotaged their lives. They probably were selfish. They may have been ready to leave their partners but they should have left then heal a bit. You take negative energy into the next if you don‚Äôt self reflect; in doing so, many family members were probably hurt. 

I think that Johnny has demons. Doesn‚Äôt anyone remember him trashing a hotel room back in the day? I believe he drinks and is still a drug user. I think she got fed up with his Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde antics. He had the means  to get therapy and I‚Äôm sure she wanted to leave. She looks like someone who is passionate and that is probably why he was attracted to her. If you never been around a drug user or someone who‚Äôs a mean drunk, don‚Äôt throw stones. It‚Äôs scary and you think you can save that person. Sober, they are lambs. Drunk, unrecognizable and dangerous. When you trap someone in the corner who has had enough, and you loose respect for each other, evil behavior will ensue. The drunk will try to control you to their will and the other will try to survive and take their fear and turn it into anger. Amber should have ran when she saw he was out of control but he was her husband. He probably lives in a yes world like Elvis did spiraling. Why didn‚Äôt his people help him. Why didn‚Äôt they remove her and get those two to heal. I believe she did hurt him and lash back at him. I believe he hurt her and didn‚Äôt take care of himself. When you‚Äôre drunk you black out. He probably has no idea how scary he was and she lost her head. I feel sorry for them and their families. I believe his exes have stories to support his violent antic. They probably are too ashamed or on the payroll. His ex will not bad mouth the father of her children but there
 is a truth here that maybe one day will come out. One being these superstars have nothing left to want. When you are hungry you strive to succeed. When you are at the top and no where else to go, you medicate to numb your loss for ‚Äúeye of the tiger!‚Äù I know it‚Äôs corney. But remember when Rocky had it all?! Apollo was there to show him the way. Where was all Johnny‚Äôs people? Why didn‚Äôt Amber‚Äôs people tell her go! Get him help but go until he‚Äôs well. People who abuse drugs eventually burn up inside and lash out when they lost all control. Johnny was afraid of his own demons. I always adored him. I pray he will find a way to love himself again. Hollywood turned their back on him? He‚Äôs made them millions! Take care of one of our treasures. Don‚Äôt abandon him. Lastly, and of course this is only my opinion. Sheer speculation. Amber is young. She‚Äôs talented and deserves to get on with her life and rebuild it. Leave them alone. She definitely needs therapy too. I wish them well.

comment: When a child experiences abuse they are often not believed because their siblings have wonderful parents and no one can fathom that a parent or family will exlcude one member at the families mutual benefit. Shit goes south well its child x fault and the cycle continues. The thing about marriage abuse is that the perpetrator usually has wonderful relationships with everyone else so no one around the couple can fathom the person being violent as the victim grows more alarmed and sees friemds and family fall and take the side of their abusor they grow more and more distressed becoming a mess and so then people rationalize that well maybe the abuser is frustrated by the victims actions because we sure all are. The victim becomes frantic and becomes farther alienated from society. The abuser stands while the victim falls in both cases. The saddest part is people who experience chikdhood abuse also experience maritial abuse and the cycle continues until they go crazy,  commit suicide, or a murdered. Think nicole brown...did she get justice or did the whole world watch and read a book about how OJ commited the deed and are we not entertained? The circus you see is evolving... this is a different form of gladiator and the strong well we know that violence is a weak minds tool and that love kindness and prayer heal these wounds. The frantic nature of the actions of a victim if the are talking about the abuse openly isnt to save themselves.. its to shine a warning that the monster you fear isnt under your bed, its the one providing you a roof over your head or the one sharing your bed with you. When you realize your dependant on those you fear for basic survival as a child and that your child are dependent on for survival as an adult well you become fearless and make it your mission to take the fall to the brinks of a corrupt justice system to ensure that the story is heard that your life is over but if you can expose even one abuser than you save their next victim and your life becomes purposeful again. If death challenges you to a duel then your allowed to dance with death and many of us do a tango with death our whole lives because as long as death is focused on us then someone else is getting to live an actual life. Death is not allowed to look away from your dance and some of us learn to dance in a fashion that death might just lose this duel. Sorry typos. Keep your eyes closed people you might not want to join the dance floor or scene johnny is on. The shadow side isnt dark or the devil is the victims who protect you.

We learn what what learn from childhood and live it out in patterns in adulthood. He left his first wife because she was not like the familiar waters of his childhood. Anyone who goes through abuse learns both roles. You know how to be the victim and you also know how to be the victimizer. Depending on your partner's programming,--aggressive or recessive, will slot you into one or the other role.

The truth lies in both of their childhood experiences.

comment:
There is a lot of Hunter S. Thompson in Johnny Depp, especially the way he conveys himself on camera off big screen. Thompson didn't write so much as he documented....the large scale over the top vocabulary, and the stitching of the words help put a fictional appearance on the truth. Completed works, life camouflaged as fiction because the thought of the context being reality is absurd if not frightening. The mind, heart and soul don't want to recognize that things could get that strange, cold and depraved. 
Most of us only believe in stories, thats what reality documented becomes to everyone but the writer. Most all of what we know today is through a story....as determination, and a true sense for knowledge through experience has been replaced with hashtags, life as someones follower. A footnote in someone elses story as apposed to the lead in ones own life.

comment:
This makes me so angry at how society pushes men to not feel or acknowledge abuse against themselves or other men. Men can and are victims of abuse just like women and non-binary people are. Gender has nothing to do with whether someone can be harmed. Saying that a man can‚Äôt be a victim to domestic abuse is just as stupid as saying a man can‚Äôt be victim to murder. I hope we can all learn from Jonny Depp‚Äôs case. He‚Äôs being very brave in fighting when all that victims of abuse want is for it to be over. He‚Äôs making great strides for men that are victims of abuse too, offering them the courage to be vocal and to be validated.
Edit: I hope this can be an opportunity to not just focus on the abuser but have empathy and make a place for the abused. Just like how the focus in police brutality shouldn‚Äôt be about the police but about recreating the system and standing up for Black lives, this is an opportunity for us to make a safe and kind space for men who have been victims and for us as a society to be honest about what women, and any other gender, are capable of. Woman are not weak, men are not just strong. Amber is an abuser, she isn‚Äôt an exception to the rule. Just like masculine abusers, she is out of control and needs to pay the consequences of being abusive. She is not special for being a woman and also an abuser. She is just a criminal who has done a lot of harmful things that are destroying the lives of those around her, just like Chris Brown and what he has done to his partners. These are monstrous actions no matter who did them. If Amber is a bitch that means that Chris Brown is a bitch too. Both cases are horrifying and special not because of which gender the abuser is of but because of who they are (popular influencers that many had respected and saw as role models) and how we love those that were abused.

comment:
My son, attend unto my wisdom, and bow thine ear to my understanding:

2¬†That thou mayest regard discretion, and that thy lips may keep knowledge.

3¬†For the lips of a strange woman drop as an honeycomb, and her mouth is smoother than oil:

4¬†But her end is bitter as wormwood, sharp as a two-edged sword.

5¬†Her feet go down to death; her steps take hold on hell.

6¬†Lest thou shouldest ponder the path of life, her ways are moveable, that thou canst not know them.

7¬†Hear me now therefore, O ye children, and depart not from the words of my mouth.

8¬†Remove thy way far from her, and come not nigh the door of her house:

9¬†Lest thou give thine honour unto others, and thy years unto the cruel:

10¬†Lest strangers be filled with thy wealth; and thy labours be in the house of a stranger;

11¬†And thou mourn at the last, when thy flesh and thy body are consumed,

12¬†And say, How have I hated instruction, and my heart despised reproof;

13¬†And have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor inclined mine ear to them that instructed me!

14¬†I was almost in all evil in the midst of the congregation and assembly.

15¬†Drink waters out of thine own cistern, and running waters out of thine own well.

16¬†Let thy fountains be dispersed abroad, and rivers of waters in the streets.

17¬†Let them be only thine own, and not strangers' with thee.

18¬†Let thy fountain be blessed: and rejoice with the wife of thy youth.

19¬†Let her be as the loving hind and pleasant roe; let her breasts satisfy thee at all times; and be thou ravished always with her love.

20¬†And why wilt thou, my son, be ravished with a strange woman, and embrace the bosom of a stranger?

21¬†For the ways of man are before the eyes of the¬†Lord, and he pondereth all his goings.

22¬†His own iniquities shall take the wicked himself, and he shall be holden with the cords of his sins.

23¬†He shall die without instruction; and in the greatness of his folly he shall go astray (Proverbs 5)

comment:
As a victim of domestic abuse I have cried for help to close friends only to be laughed at and hear them say the line I have heard countless times " what? Who Chloe? Come on Mark you're twice her size."
  Yes I am but, I don't care what size you are when your partner changes in a second and throws a tantrum of dramatic proportion you are confused not mad, you don't become violent when someone you love attacks you, and says I want to kill you or my feeling of hate for you are growing... you become sad, heart broke. Confused. However, when you are involved in gaslighting and victim play, we all know gaslighting but victim play is when you are bated into an argument led into a shouting match and when you least expect it they change into the victim and wilt in your shadow as you begin to see the game is afoot. Trauma bonding, gas lighting, pathology, compulsive behavior, two faced, baring, compartmentalizing, remorseless, lack of empathy, I have seen it all. And yet I have been to the hospital twice, had my nose broken twice, 11 stitches to my lower lip, had my toes broken and big toe nail broken of entirely under a door that was forced open when I was hiding in the bathroom. I have been betrayed and made out to be a monster to my own circle if friends through rumors and gossip she started. Talking behind my back and defaming my name to everyone and the corner store clerk. Everyone began looking at me differently. I have taken to drugs and isolating myself. Lost work (musician BTW). Neighbors all avoid me. And she's the victim right? The only one who has a life anymore, friends, family, local relations with shop owners, exes, my friends without me. Also, had one car stoled twice, the next car stolen once. My property in our home missing as if stolen only to reappear out of the blue somewhere I clearly looked already. And items appear in the house that do not belong to me and when asked she responds "I don't know that's not mine" she would say about that. I have been followed, called paranoid, but there is nothing more pathetic than a sloppy Snoop. And caught red handed, countless times. Who are these people. Sorry, but I understand Johnny's case, but me. I am nobody with nothing. This is sickness, and for what, it's torture for no gains. Bye.

comment: Take some notes, feminists. Your generalisation of an entire gender is vapid in the extreme. But it sells books and promotional tours. I was groomed by my mother to despise my father. He was an alcoholic who flew into rages and was often violent. My mother would use me as an intermediary, in which times she felt powerful and gave him hell and made the problems worse. I didn't realise it at the time. Now I can look back and see the whole picture but I can't take back the way I treated my father by proxy, even though he hurt me, too. Your gender doesn't automatically make you a suppliant and relationships, even back in the "old days" were more complex. If we can get more books about the whole picture, maybe there can be more healing.

comment:
All things considered- come on, just break them down separately. Johnny has had a wonderful career that has spanned literally decades. He has known fame & fortune because of who he is & the character's he's played. He's lived his life with relationships along the way with some more attention grabbing than others. Including having & raising children along the way. He's not an Angel & has never claimed to be. But he's always shown a fabulous sense of gratitude toward his fans along the way. Everyone has a held him in a very high regard. I think it was David Letterman that said, You meet him to do the interview, hang out, talk & laugh. Then when he goes you realize there's something missing in your life & you just want him to come back. Because he's someone you want to be around all the time & have him in your life. 
Even his exes speak highly of him. There haven't been any instances of violence with him against any of his exes. They have even remained friends. You have to admit that's pretty telling.
Then you have Amber.... Didn't know anything about her until she got with Johnny. I do think that he fell for her. I also think that she looked at him as way to get what she wanted, fame & fortune.  She, including family & friends, used Johnny as much as they could to pay for everything. She has a history of domestic violence with her family & ex-partners. The recordings that came to light were unbelievable. She even had an ex-lover living at one of the places that Johnny paid for & he was upset that she was there. But still tolerated it for her. In those recordings she belittled Johnny for not fighting back. For not tolerating her hitting/punching/slapping him. Criticized him for walking away, saying he would run away! Instead of staying in his own house & fighting with her. He & the body guards had it worked out so far as to how they would escape! Because they never knew what kind of mood she was going to be in. There are photos of where she severed his finger & burned his face with a cigarette! She lied to police & falsified police reports. Every instance of violence & destruction was proved to be false by people who were there or people that cleaned the areas later. Then of course the incidents that happened in Australia!
We CANNOT forget the way she bragged about donating the $7,000,000!! Can't forget how she Jumped on the ME TOO!! band wagon with her lies! She even stooped so low as to STEAL the tragic attack & abuse story of another woman!! A woman that was supposed to be her friend & claim it as her own!! She lied under oath over & over again!!
I honestly hate that someone as sweet as Johnny had to go through any kind of ill treatment! Let alone it coming from the one person that you would hope would consider him more precious than anything else on the planet!! I don't understand it!
I hope & pray people see this FUKN' POS for what she truly is & toss her out like the trash she is!!! #JUSTICEFORJOHNNY!!!

comment: It's extremely sad that we're at a point where the media can print one side of a story... An accusation with no evidence, is enough to destroy someone's life before they've even stepped in a court room. The media has way too much power, it completely undermines the idea of due process and justice. I don't care what you're being accused of, an accusation should never be the be all end all. Not this "you know your truth, whatever that is" absolute nonsense. There is no "your truth" or "my truth", only THE truth and the media seem to believe the truth is relative to whoever speaks first. The scary part is that in a case like this, even if Depp turns the whole thing around and reveals her to be the monster she always claimed he was.... It's not in the media's best interests to admit they got something wrong because it shows them as irresponsible, unethical journalists, so you know full well they will not give the same coverage to Johnny Depp being innocent as they have done Johnny Depp 'probably' being guilty.

comment:
As a male being an abuse victim is first embarrassing which most female abusers rely on(there is no help or support available for male abuse victims). Sadly the laws and mentality in most places empower female abusers.  
Second you are still trying to figure everything out like "why is this person I love and says they love me doing this to me. What should I do about it?" 
Third you become disconnected and start looking for an escape to help you cope with the situation i.e. the drugs, alcohol, looking for any work that will keep you busy doing something else. 
Fourth is downplay the true pain you are feeling while subconsciously sending out messages for help. Fifth is plotting the escape from the abuser. Sadly the abuser normally is furious about the escape and will seek vengeance short of absolute destruction of the abused by any means possible.

Answer to any abusive relationship is simple... Do whatever it takes to remove yourself asap... It can get better after that.
Allways a new light at the end of the tunnel. Always a new day to start over.
Male or female 
Abuse is not worth it no matter how much love you "think" you feel.
Good luck everyone. üëåüíóüëå

In turn, they abusive behaviour is usually rooted in their upbringing. I know VERY well what I am talking about. I have suffered myself abuse from my adoptive father for my whole life. Just as my mother did. He was also sexually abused and beaten repeatedly in a horrible religious school in the 50s. And not only that but later in life I surprised myself reproducing similar toxic patterns in my relationships, despite not having his genetics. After that discovery I decided that I am not in this world to hurt nobody and commited to remove that crap from me, never behave like my father again. That was many years ago. I would walk away one time after another because those twisted mechanisms rooted in my past kept emerging and I will stay alone if necessary. We all have the power to be who you want to be. Being rigurous in your self analysis is key to change. That's how I try my best. Perhaps someone else can make something out of it. The JD story has impacted me deeply because I saw so many things of my own in it. Good luck everybody, I love u all and I wish u the best in your walk of life, whatever your choices or demons are.
